body:
# Repository Settings

Configure repository behavior, access controls, and branch policies.

## General Settings

```javascript
import { Octokit } from "@octokit/rest";
const octokit = new Octokit({ auth: process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN });

// Update repo settings
await octokit.repos.update({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  description: "Updated description",
  default_branch: "main",
  has_issues: true,
  has_wiki: false,
  has_projects: false,
  allow_squash_merge: true,
  allow_merge_commit: false,
  allow_rebase_merge: true,
  allow_auto_merge: true,
  delete_branch_on_merge: true,
  squash_merge_commit_title: "PR_TITLE",
  squash_merge_commit_message: "PR_BODY",
});
```

```bash
# gh CLI — update settings via API
gh api repos/owner/repo -X PATCH \
  -f default_branch=main \
  -F allow_squash_merge=true \
  -F delete_branch_on_merge=true
```

## Branch Protection

```javascript
// Set branch protection rules
await octokit.repos.updateBranchProtection({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  branch: "main",
  required_status_checks: {
    strict: true,   // Require branch to be up to date before merging
    contexts: ["ci/test", "ci/lint"],  // Required check names from Actions
  },
  enforce_admins: true,
  required_pull_request_reviews: {
    required_approving_review_count: 1,
    dismiss_stale_reviews: true,
    require_code_owner_reviews: true,
    dismissal_restrictions: {
      users: [],
      teams: ["maintainers"],
    },
  },
  restrictions: null,  // null = no push restrictions
  required_linear_history: true,
  allow_force_pushes: false,
  allow_deletions: false,
  required_conversation_resolution: true,
});

// Get current branch protection
const { data: protection } = await octokit.repos.getBranchProtection({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  branch: "main",
});
console.log(protection.required_status_checks.contexts);

// Delete branch protection
await octokit.repos.deleteBranchProtection({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  branch: "main",
});
```

```bash
# gh CLI — set branch protection
gh api repos/owner/repo/branches/main/protection -X PUT \
  --input - <<EOF
{
  "required_status_checks": {
    "strict": true,
    "contexts": ["ci/test"]
  },
  "enforce_admins": true,
  "required_pull_request_reviews": {
    "required_approving_review_count": 1
  },
  "restrictions": null
}
EOF
```

## Collaborators

```javascript
// Add a collaborator
await octokit.repos.addCollaborator({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  username: "new-collaborator",
  permission: "push",  // pull, push, admin, maintain, triage
});

// List collaborators
const { data: collabs } = await octokit.repos.listCollaborators({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
});

// Remove a collaborator
await octokit.repos.removeCollaborator({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  username: "former-collaborator",
});
```

```bash
# gh CLI — manage collaborators
gh api repos/owner/repo/collaborators/username -X PUT -f permission=push
```

## CODEOWNERS

Automate review assignment by file path:

```
# .github/CODEOWNERS
* @default-team
/src/api/ @api-team
/src/auth/ @security-team
/docs/ @docs-team
*.go @go-team
```

CODEOWNERS works with branch protection's "Require review from Code Owners" setting.

## Merge Options

| Setting | Effect |
|---------|--------|
| `allow_merge_commit` | Allow merge commit strategy |
| `allow_squash_merge` | Allow squash merge strategy |
| `allow_rebase_merge` | Allow rebase merge strategy |
| `allow_auto_merge` | Allow auto-merge when checks pass |
| `delete_branch_on_merge` | Auto-delete head branches after merge |
| `squash_merge_commit_title` | `PR_TITLE` or `COMMIT_OR_PR_TITLE` |
| `squash_merge_commit_message` | `PR_BODY`, `COMMIT_MESSAGES`, or `BLANK` |
